  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / About</div>
      <h1>We Build Software the Way We'd Want It Built For Us.</h1>
      <p>Adalyn Technologies designs and builds custom software, digital platforms, and business systems for organizations that are done running on spreadsheets, WhatsApp, and manual processes.</p>
      <p style="font-size:14px; color:var(--gold3); font-weight:600; margin-top:-6px;">1,000+ students &middot; 700+ customers &middot; Systems live in production since 2024</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="what-grid">
        <div class="what-text">
          <span class="section-label">Founder's Note</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">From a Single School System to a Growing Platform</h2>
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px; margin-bottom:18px;">
            <img src="mercy-mbaka.jpg" alt="Mercy K. Mbaka, Founder" style="width:64px; height:64px; border-radius:50%; object-fit:cover; border:2px solid var(--gold);">
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block; color:var(--navy); font-size:15px;">Mercy K. Mbaka</strong>
              <span style="font-size:13px; color:var(--gray);">Founder, Adalyn Technologies</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>I started Adalyn Technologies after watching a school lose money and trust to a fee-collection process held together by paper receipts and phone calls. I built a system to fix that specific problem - not a generic school app, a direct answer to what that school was actually struggling with.</p>
          <p>That system is now running live for over 1,000 students, and the way I built it became the way I build everything: understand the operational problem first, then design software around how the organization actually works - not the other way around.</p>
          <p>Today Adalyn Technologies partners with schools, businesses, and startups across Kenya to build systems that hold up under real, daily use - and we stay on after launch, because software that isn't maintained is software that quietly starts failing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="what-services">
          <h4>How We Work</h4>
          <ul class="what-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> We start with your operational problem, not a technology choice</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> We design for how your team actually works day to day</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> We build for production load, not a demo</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> We document everything we hand over</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> We stay on for support after launch</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-navy">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header section-center">
        <span class="section-label">Who We Are</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Mission, Vision & Values</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="mv-grid">
        <div class="mv-card anim">
          <i class="fas fa-bullseye"></i>
          <h3>Mission</h3>
          <p>To design reliable digital solutions that help organizations operate more efficiently, innovate confidently, and achieve sustainable growth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mv-card anim">
          <i class="fas fa-eye"></i>
          <h3>Vision</h3>
          <p>To become one of Africa's most trusted software engineering companies, known for building technology that creates lasting value for businesses, institutions, and communities.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mv-card anim">
          <i class="fas fa-heart"></i>
          <h3>Values</h3>
          <p>The principles behind every project we take on.</p>
          <div class="values-row">
            <span class="value-chip">Excellence</span>
            <span class="value-chip">Integrity</span>
            <span class="value-chip">Craftsmanship</span>
            <span class="value-chip">Long-Term Partnership</span>
            <span class="value-chip">Client Success</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header section-center">
        <span class="section-label">Milestones</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Where We've Been, Where We're Going</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item anim">
          <div class="timeline-year">2024</div>
          <div class="timeline-body">
            <h4>First Production System</h4>
            <p>Built and deployed our first school management system to solve a real fee-collection problem - the foundation of what became our School ERP product.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item anim">
          <div class="timeline-year">2025</div>
          <div class="timeline-body">
            <h4>Expanding Into Business & Agritech</h4>
            <p>Delivered the Adalyn Sales system and an e-commerce platform for an agritech client, growing beyond education into general business tooling.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item anim">
          <div class="timeline-year">Today</div>
          <div class="timeline-body">
            <h4>1,000+ Students, 700+ Customers Served</h4>
            <p>Our systems now run live in production across multiple institutions and businesses, with ongoing hosting, maintenance, and support contracts.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item anim">
          <div class="timeline-year">Next</div>
          <div class="timeline-body">
            <h4>Growing Our Product Suite</h4>
            <p>We're investing in new products including KidLearn, alongside continued custom development for schools, startups, and enterprise clients.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

